    {
      "id": "73e94685_693034f0",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/controller/NetworkCmProxyControllerSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "I think there was a good reason we had a separate 'deprecated' rest endpoint (check with Dylan) E might need some discussion on this!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6639,
        "name": "Toine Siebelink",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "toine.siebelink@est.tech",
        "username": "ToineSiebelink"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-31 16:42:31.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "469d60d9_c9a62121",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-rest/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/ncmp/rest/controller/NetworkCmProxyControllerSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 70,
      "message": "In this test class, we were referring base path in three ways\n\n1. deprecatedDataNodeBaseEndPoint = $basePath/v1 -> old endpoints.\n2. ncmpDmiEndpoint = $basePath/ncmp-dmi/v1 -> only dmi registration because the endpoint was not different from others. After the change both deprecatedDataNodeBaseEndPoint and ncmpDmiEndpoint are same.\n3. basePath =  $basePath -> in the passthrough endpoint test cases.\n\nWith the new api change, we can use the same path for all three and I believe it is an improvement over what we had before.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2021-08-31 17:49:41.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "73e94685_693034f0",
      "unresolved": true
    },
